Sector: The Sector the Company is operating in
Industry: The Industry the Company is operating in
FiscalYearEnd: The end of the fiscal year
MarketCapitalization: The Market Capitalization of the Company
EBITDA: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization
PERatio: Price to Earnings ratio (Price per share / earnins per share)
PEGRatio: Price to Earnings ratio divided by Earnings per share growth (PE Ratio / EPS Growth)
BookValue: The value of a security or asset as entered in a firm's books.
DividendPerShare: The amount of a dividend paid per share.
DividendYield: The ratio of a company's dividend payments to its net income.
RevenuePerShareTTM: Revenue per share trailing twelve months (TTM)
ProfitMargin: The ratio of the net sales - cost of goods sold and Net sales (Net sales - COGS / Net sales).
OperatingMarginTTM: The percentage of revenue remaining after paying all operating expenses trailing twelve months(TTM)
ReturnOnAssetsTTM: The net income of the company divided by the total assets of the company (Net income / Total assets).
ReturnOnEquityTTM: The income Available to Common Stockholders for the trailing twelve months divided by the Average Common Equity expressed as a percentage
RevenueTTM: The total revenue trailing twelve months
